content.description:
SDS with both of your hands on a pod feature to the right of

Evil Seed

. A difficult first move leads into a compression sequence. Top out on

Evil Seed

. Bring a very thin pad to protect the first move. Unless you are able to commit to a more difficult sequence, avoiding the dab can be problematic.
content.location:
It is on the right side of the face at the high part of the hill which comprises the landing of

Evil Seed

.

content.description: Start standing with your left hand on a sloping edge and your right hand on an incut sidepull. A compression sequence culminates in a large throw out right. Top out the prow on the right side of the face.
content.location: This is on the right side of the face.

content.description: SDS on the pod feature on the right side of the face. Make a large and powerful first move, and climb into the stand. Bring a very thin pad to protect the first move. Unless you are able to commit to a more difficult sequence, avoiding the dab can be problematic.
content.location: It is on the right side of the face.

content.description:
Climb through the right exit after starting as per Austin Purdy's original

Treebeard

.

Start with your right hand on a crimp at the top of the pod of the SDS, and with your left hand on a large, sloping edge at approximately 4-5 feet high. Note that the left hand starting edge is not the large sloping pod feature out left. Climb into

Return of the Mossman

.
content.location: It is on the right side of the face.

content.description:
This is a compression piece.

Per Eric Lang's vimeo: "stand is starting in the finger crack/jug right in the middle of the overhang. Evil Seed is the sit and starts down and left."
content.location: Park on the creekside just before Tunnel 6. Cross the road, go over the guard rail, and it is up the hill about maybe 100 yards on the right.

content.description:
Sit and start down and left of

Return Of The Moss Man

.
content.location: Park on the creekside just before Tunnel 6. Cross the road, go over the guardrail, and it is up the hill about maybe 100 yards on the right.

content.description: This is a low angle face climb with some small crimps and slopers.
content.location: If you are looking at Moss Man from below, hike left, and angle up the hill slightly ~ 150 yards away from Moss Man.
